en: Toledo 1970.2
comparanda
On boar hunts, cf. La Coste Messelire, Au Muse de Delphes, Paris 1936, pp. 120-152; von Bothmer, 1948, BMFA Bulletin 46, no. 264, pp. 42-48; and Schnarp, A., 1979, Revue Archologique, pp. 195 ff..
condit

Flaked red and black glaze retouched, especially on the foot. A small fault on side A, to the left of the boar's eye, and a second one on the chest of the panther below the boar have been replastered and repainted.
